  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first let me say that, after my first home with the young Frenchwoman and young British woman, then I wasn't there very long before I moved to a large mansion on Hebelstrasse-- three full levels-- where I lived with two American court reporters, Ann Daniels and Dorothy Fitzgerald, who were good friends.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We became very good friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this house was right across the street from the house in-- on Hebelstrasse-- in which-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] It's back here.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the house on Hebelstrasse, in which [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Spencer Tracy was filmed, Judge-- filmed-- was filmed in a huge home.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then after that, we tried to get into the Grand Hotel as soon as we could.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I went-- I lived in the Grand Hotel on the fourth floor, where the greatest security was.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From there, it was easy for us to, to get together in the lobby of the Grand Hotel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now remember, I told you that [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] there was no heat anywhere.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we didn't have any hot water to take baths or showers in, only ice cold water, and no heat at all.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had feather beds.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in the Grand Hotel, even before I moved there, when we got out of court, what we had heard during that day was so horrifying that none of us wanted to go back to our particular rooms in my first home to be alone at night.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And therefore, we all-- and we had to go somewhere for an army mess.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in, in the big mansion, the army actually had a mess in our grand ballroom on the fourth-- first floor.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't know who owned-- which-- what Germans were displaced, you know, who owned that house.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
